OL,3,CUlster Farmers' Union takes no
OL,4,Cconfidence vote in DAERA
OL,6,F"The UFU had continued to engage with
OL,7,Fthe department in good faith,
OL,8,Fremaining patient and hopeful that co-
OL,9,Foperation would yield results, but
OL,10,Ffelt this was not being reciprocated
OL,11,Fby Daera.
OL,13,F"From wildlife intervention to tackle
OL,14,Fbovine tuberculosis (bTB), ammonia
OL,15,Fcontrols and planning in relation to
OL,16,Fthe nutrients action programme, sheep
OL,17,Fsector support and a generational
OL,18,Frenewal scheme under the sustainable
OL,19,Ffarming programme, Daera is failing to
OL,20,Fdeliver for the farming industry."
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOU|D@bO]
